narratives.question_text: What knowledge, skills, and insights did you develop by taking this course?
comments: Learned basic econometrics and basics of R.
A better understanding of statistical practices.

programming language R
analytical skills

While I took this course with the intent to learn new econometric skills to be used in the course of research, I actually learned more about the mathematics behind the research methods I already employ such as regressions.
The mathematical foundation of statistics and the application of statistics to solve real world problem.
I leaned a lot about the basics of statistics as well as some of the basics of coding in R.

narratives.question_text: What are the strengths and weaknesses of this course and how could it be improved?
comments: Some parts of the course felt less introductory, assuming that we already knew certain things that were not prerequisite knowledge.
time constraint, it's hard for students to learn a new programming language and understand the concepts within one month.
This course could be improved by focusing on more real-world applications of econometrics rather than the theoretical mathematical proofs involved.
It would be great if there is more opportunity to conduct practical projects in statistics.
The problem sets were particularly difficult at the beginning since there was very little tutorial on how to use R for beginners.

narratives.question_text: Would you recommend this course to another student? Please explain.
comments: Not during the summer, as it is a lot to cram into one month.
Yes. It was an interesting course that seemed to have a lot of practical applications.

Yes, I would recommend this course to another economics student as econometrics is fundamental for research. I would warn them though that this course is far from comprehensive and is more theory based than application based.
Yes.
I probably would not recommend this class to another student unless they were somewhat comfortable with statistics or coding since a lot of this information was assumed on behalf of the student.
